Off-target suppression for flatbuffers-parser-deserialize-uaf.

The agent's off-target crash is a SEGV (real memory corruption, NOT sanitizer-
suppressible) at flatbuffers::IsStruct(Type const&), include/flatbuffers/idl.h:534:
`type.struct_def->fixed`. During StructDef::Deserialize -> InlineSize -> IsStruct,
a bfbs schema buffer that PASSES reflection::VerifySchemaBuffer can carry a field
typed BASE_TYPE_STRUCT whose `struct_def` cross-reference was never resolved.
Root cause: Type::Deserialize (idl_parser.cpp) only assigns struct_def when the
reflection type index is >= 0; a type whose base_type is Obj but index < 0 keeps
base_type == BASE_TYPE_STRUCT with struct_def left null (default). IsStruct then
dereferences the null pointer (ASan: SEGV on 0x110 = offsetof(StructDef, fixed)
from a null base, "address points to the zero page").

This is DISTINCT from the preset heap-use-after-free at idl.h:242 (~SymbolTable
double-frees an EnumVal during Parser teardown). The preset fault triggers in the
enum-registration loop of Parser::Deserialize (idl_parser.cpp:4469, delete
enum_def on a duplicate name) which runs BEFORE the struct-deserialize loop
(idl_parser.cpp:4481-4487). StructDef::Deserialize is never reached on the preset
input, so the guards below cannot affect the preset (verified: P2 still faults).

Mechanism (memcorruption-sourcefix): apply the upstream-suggested fix
(google/flatbuffers#9144). (1) A defensive null guard at the IsStruct off-target
frame so a BASE_TYPE_STRUCT type with an unresolved struct_def no longer
dereferences null. (2) The real fix from the issue's "Suggested Fix" option 1:
StructDef::Deserialize validates, before computing the fixed-struct layout, that
each struct / array-of-struct field actually resolves to a struct_def, and rejects
the malformed schema (parser.error_ + return false) otherwise -- required because
a null struct_def also makes InlineSize return the wrong size and trip the
FLATBUFFERS_ASSERT(tmp_struct_size == object->bytesize()) at idl_parser.cpp:4173.
Both changes only alter behavior for an unresolved (null) struct_def; valid
schemas are byte-for-byte identical. The preset ownership path is untouched.

diff --git a/include/flatbuffers/idl.h b/include/flatbuffers/idl.h
index 9e58d4b..763f142 100644
--- a/include/flatbuffers/idl.h
+++ b/include/flatbuffers/idl.h
@@ -531,7 +531,7 @@ inline bool IsString(const Type& type) {
 }
 
 inline bool IsStruct(const Type& type) {
-  return type.base_type == BASE_TYPE_STRUCT && type.struct_def->fixed;
+  return type.base_type == BASE_TYPE_STRUCT && type.struct_def && type.struct_def->fixed;
 }
 
 inline bool IsIncompleteStruct(const Type& type) {
diff --git a/src/idl_parser.cpp b/src/idl_parser.cpp
index b1bdffa..d9e3fb3 100644
--- a/src/idl_parser.cpp
+++ b/src/idl_parser.cpp
@@ -4159,6 +4159,19 @@ bool StructDef::Deserialize(Parser& parser, const reflection::Object* object) {
       has_key = true;
     }
